This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with parsing English sentences into Abstract Meaning Representation (AMR). It also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as SEARN, which is commonly used in natural language processing. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as these fields are closely related to natural language processing and machine learning.
